column11:
The main service is the company's application of plant protection products and fertilizers to various agricultural crops using agrotrons. The use of technology solves the following tasks: 
- Application of pesticides to tall crops (corn, sunflower), avoiding trampling and crop loss (3-20%);
- saving water (about 90%) according to classical technology;
- increasing yield (accurately, on time);
- the ability to apply products in wet soil, when the rest of the equipment is ineffective
- saving on equipment (60-90% on services)
- consideration of the problem of lack of qualified personnel (agrodrones are quite easy to use) 
We also sell agrodrones, provide service services for their repair, and also teach how to use them, which ensures the development and popularization of technologies. 
Another direction of the company is the selection of soil samples for analysis and selection of fertilizers. This service ensures efficient use of resources, increased yields, environmentally friendly use of resources, and minimizing the use of chemical fertilizers.

- Businesses, especially in agriculture and suburban and periurban areas, face rising electricity costs, unstable grid supply, and limited access to clean energy. Solar alone cannot provide 24/7 power — leaving a gap during nighttime, cloudy seasons, and winter months when agricultural operations (cold storage, irrigation, climate-controlled greenhouses) still demand continuous energy.

- Sirocco Energy develops a patented linear-motion wind turbine designed specifically for distributed energy generation in suburban and peri-urban environments (with average wind speed of 5+ m/s).

- designed for the suburban wind speed (average of 5+ m/s);
linear blade movement with shorter blades, that are mounted at two points;
smaller installation footprint (3x times less space comparing to traditional wind turbine, up to 10x times less for several turbines installed);
low noise and vibration;
optimized for easy logistics (30kW version of turbine fits into standard container);
safe for birds.

LCOE - $0,03 to $0,08 cents/kW
Cuts electricity costs by 2–5× with a 2–7 year payback period
Modular and scalable
Reduces dependence on grid and diesel generators, works complementary with solar, improving overall system stability and year-round generation
